  "instructions": [
    "Heat a large pot over medium heat. Add pork back ribs, ginger, garlic, black pepper, cumin, and salt. Cook for 10 minutes until pork is slightly tender.",
    "In a small bowl, mix tadka oil, red wine vinegar, and fresh thyme. Heat the mixture until the oil is shimmering (tempering).",
    "Remove pork from the pot and add the tadka mixture to the pot. Return pork to the pot and cook for 5 minutes until the pork is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Let rest for 10 minutes before serving with a side of mashed potatoes or green beans."
  ],
